<li><b><u>As Covid-19 outbreak slows down, some CEM churches have resumed or are scheduled to resume Sunday Services.</u></b><br/>
	<ul>
		<li>  CEC churches in Spain:
			<ol>
				<li>CEC Benidorm has resumed Sunday Services on 5/31 at 9 pm. However, the Wednesday night and Friday night Bible Study at 9 pm are still online.
				</li>
				<li> CEC Madrid has resumed Sunday Services on 6/7 but the online service is still available because only 1/3 of the congregation is allowed into the church due to social distancing.
				</li>			    
				<li> CEC South Madrid has resumed Sunday Services on 6/7 at 10:30 am, and at 5:30 pm		</li>
				<li> CEC Usera has resumed Saturday church Services on 6/13 but online service will still be available.			
				</li>
				<li>CEC Fuenbrada has resumed Sunday Services on 6/14 but online service will still be available.		    		    
				</li>
				<li> CEC Valencia has resumed Sunday Services on 6/14.	</li>		
				<li> CEC Gran Canaria has resumed Sunday Services on 6/7 at church. The Bible Study in the South is held at church as well. But the Bible Study in the North will continue to watch the video.	</li>		
				<li> CEC Barcelona has resumed Sunday Services on 6/14. However, online Sunday service will still be available; and the Bible Study on Tuesday and Thursday are still online.	</li>		
			</ol>
		</li> <br/>
	
		<li> CEC churches in South Africa:
			<ol>
				<li> The three churches in South Africa have resumed Sunday services by holding a combined service in CEC Cape Town on 6/7 at 3 pm. There are no services in CEC Welington, nor in CEC Parow-Noord until the Covid-19 is outbreak under control.
				</li>	
			</ol>
		</li>
	</ul><br/>
